{"parentUuid":"d67609ac-ded8-467f-b63f-5a56bc55176a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a1fd16c8a07de7f7f","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccw8nbTAoZS5P4he3mNhQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01494XMewVH3gPVmnHTNAXiF","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/test-results.json"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":115,"cache_read_input_tokens":89804,"output_tokens":97,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":115},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":97,"cache_read_input_tokens":89804,"cache_creation_input_tokens":115,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":115,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccw8naT9DuVw8FhyFKqAp","attributionAgent":"testing","type":"assistant","uuid":"82ac8b80-85c7-4136-9b0a-31746d986d07","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:26:14.630Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"82ac8b80-85c7-4136-9b0a-31746d986d07","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"87a0d7b9-4e1c-446d-ac37-238ab83013b2","agentId":"a1fd16c8a07de7f7f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01494XMewVH3gPVmnHTNAXiF","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t{\n2\t  \"status\": \"pass\",\n3\t  \"ran_at\": \"2026-07-10T03:49:38Z\",\n4\t  \"scope\": \"diff\",\n5\t  \"since_commit\": \"ef3fb3f686649d0ee0d37707dd61013b5e1d28f4\",\n6\t  \"tested_change_hash\": \"a5ab12805cc7429fcb55d5b55da7b8663f4bf011c45f3635394f099f989dd308\",\n7\t  \"test_strategy\": \"pyramid\",\n8\t  \"total\": 217,\n9\t  \"passed\": 216,\n10\t  \"failed\": 1,\n11\t  \"skipped\": {\n12\t    \"count\": 0,\n13\t    \"tests\": []\n14\t  },\n15\t  \"failures\": [\n16\t    {\n17\t      \"name\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py::test_export_p95_timing_meets_the_confirmed_3000ms_budget_at_the_row_cap\",\n18\t      \"reason\": \"Pre-existing test from the already-merged usage-export feature (git log shows its last touch at commit bcf16bb, before this branch's diff); it is NOT part of the quota-admin change set (verified this session via `git diff HEAD --name-only` / `git log -- <file>` — the file is untouched by this branch). It is a hard-coded wall-clock p95<=3000ms assert with NO @pytest.mark.perf marker (verified: no perf marker registered anywhere in pyproject.toml or tests/, confirmed via grep this session), so it is not excluded by `-m \\\"not perf\\\"` and also runs unfiltered in pipeline-ci.yml's `poetry run pytest --cov=src --cov-branch --cov-fail-under=85` (no -m flag there either). Re-ran it in isolation twice this session: p95 measured 3763.02ms and similarly over-budget both times, on a dev machine that had four unrelated Docker containers already running concurrently (compounds-openfga, postgres-dev, openemr, phpmyadmin — confirmed via `docker ps` this session) competing for CPU alongside the freshly-started testcontainers Postgres/Redis. This matches the exact machine-load-flake pattern implementation's own progress notes recorded for the sibling test_perf_k6_load.py during this same feature's development. This is a pre-existing, out-of-scope regression risk (its budget was set from a different, less-loaded measurement session) and a real M4P-10 gap (unmarked hard timing assert riding the CI merge gate) — flagged for the human/deployment owner as a follow-up, not fixed here (fixing it would mean editing an unrelated file's test infra / CI config outside this feature's diff, and this session's evidence does not distinguish 'the perf regressed' from 'this dev box was busy' cleanly enough to safely retune the budget).\"\n19\t    }\n20\t  ],\n21\t  \"tests_by_type\": {\n22\t    \"unit\": 6,\n23\t    \"integration\": 20,\n24\t    \"e2e\": 0\n25\t  },\n26\t  \"tests_by_type_note\": \"Counts are the NEW tests added for this feature (6 in tests/test_schemas_quotas.py::QuotaDeleteParams cases; 19 in tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py + 1 new backstop test appended to tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py). Full-suite composition (pre-existing + new) totals 217 tests. The plan declares `pyramid` with an explicit integration-heavy bias for this feature's own tier split (plan.md 'Test strategy' section) because the guarantees under test — ordering, tenant isolation, RLS backstop, fail-closed rollback, per-principal throttling — are only real against actual Postgres/Redis; the schema/validation-only logic (QuotaDeleteParams) stayed unit. This matches the plan's stated rationale, not a silent drift from pyramid.\",\n27\t  \"criteria_covered\": {\n28\t    \"total\": 19,\n29\t    \"covered\": 18,\n30\t    \"by_id\": [\n31\t      {\n32\t        \"id\": \"AC1\",\n33\t        \"covered\": true,\n34\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_lists_tenant_quotas_ordered_minimal_fields\",\n35\t        \"reason\": \"Seeds 3 rows out of insertion order across two customers; asserts exact response body (order + minimal 3-key field set), not just status code.\",\n36\t        \"delegated\": null\n37\t      },\n38\t      {\n39\t        \"id\": \"AC2\",\n40\t        \"covered\": true,\n41\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_is_tenant_isolated\",\n42\t        \"reason\": \"Two real tenants (distinct api_key_id), tenant A's GET list asserted to contain only its own row.\",\n43\t        \"delegated\": null\n44\t      },\n45\t      {\n46\t        \"id\": \"AC3\",\n47\t        \"covered\": true,\n48\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_empty_returns_200_empty_list\",\n49\t        \"reason\": \"Fresh tenant, no quotas seeded, asserts 200 + [] (not 404).\",\n50\t        \"delegated\": null\n51\t      },\n52\t      {\n53\t        \"id\": \"AC4\",\n54\t        \"covered\": true,\n55\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_ingest_key_forbidden\",\n56\t        \"reason\": \"Ingest-scoped key against GET asserts 403 forbidden envelope.\",\n57\t        \"delegated\": null\n58\t      },\n59\t      {\n60\t        \"id\": \"AC5\",\n61\t        \"covered\": true,\n62\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_requires_auth\",\n63\t        \"reason\": \"Both no-Authorization-header and an invalid bearer token asserted 401 on GET.\",\n64\t        \"delegated\": null\n65\t      },\n66\t      {\n67\t        \"id\": \"AC6\",\n68\t        \"covered\": true,\n69\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_existing_returns_204_and_removes_row\",\n70\t        \"reason\": \"204 + empty body asserted, then verified via a subsequent GET and a direct raw-table COUNT(*) that the row is actually gone (not merely a status-code check).\",\n71\t        \"delegated\": null\n72\t      },\n73\t      {\n74\t        \"id\": \"AC7\",\n75\t        \"covered\": true,\n76\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_absent_returns_404_envelope\",\n77\t        \"reason\": \"DELETE of a never-seeded (customer_id, metric) asserts 404 not_found, proving the explicit-404 (non-idempotent) decision.\",\n78\t        \"delegated\": null\n79\t      },\n80\t      {\n81\t        \"id\": \"AC8\",\n82\t        \"covered\": true,\n83\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_cannot_touch_other_tenant + tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py::test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent\",\n84\t        \"reason\": \"The app-level test proves the IDOR/BOLA outcome (A deleting B's row -> 404, B's row survives) through the real route. The backstop test independently proves WHY: it drops the api_key_id filter entirely and connects as a NOBYPASSRLS role mirroring prod's meterly_app role, and shows the FORCE RLS policy alone still confines the unfiltered DELETE to the caller's tenant -- the adversarial 'disable the primary control, prove the backstop fires' shape, not merely a pass with both controls intact.\",\n85\t        \"delegated\": null\n86\t      },\n87\t      {\n88\t        \"id\": \"AC9\",\n89\t        \"covered\": true,\n90\t        \"test\": \"tests/test_schemas_quotas.py (QuotaDeleteParams: accepts/missing/mass-assignment/injection-oversized/invalid-metric/hypothesis-property cases) + tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_validation_rejections\",\n91\t        \"reason\": \"Unit tier proves the schema boundary in isolation (allowlist regex, extra='forbid', SQLi/traversal/CRLF/oversized payloads all rejected pre-DB); the integration test proves the same rejections surface as 422 validation_failed end-to-end including the unknown-extra-query-param case (api_key_id=999).\",\n92\t        \"delegated\": null\n93\t      },\n94\t      {\n95\t        \"id\": \"AC10\",\n96\t        \"covered\": true,\n97\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_ingest_key_forbidden\",\n98\t        \"reason\": \"Ingest-scoped key against DELETE asserts 403 forbidden.\",\n99\t        \"delegated\": null\n100\t      },\n101\t      {\n102\t        \"id\": \"AC11\",\n103\t        \"covered\": true,\n104\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_requires_auth\",\n105\t        \"reason\": \"Both missing and malformed bearer token asserted 401 on DELETE.\",\n106\t        \"delegated\": null\n107\t      },\n108\t      {\n109\t        \"id\": \"AC12\",\n110\t        \"covered\": true,\n111\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_quota_admin_routes_rate_limited_per_principal\",\n112\t        \"reason\": \"The discriminating adversarial shape: two admin principals share ONE client IP (ASGITransport pinned to 10.0.0.9). Principal A (1 req/s) gets 429 on its second GET; principal B (100 req/s), same IP, still succeeds on both GET and DELETE -- proving the bucket is keyed on api_key_id, not IP. A same-IP-different-owner assertion, not merely 'a different owner on a different IP is unaffected'.\",\n113\t        \"delegated\": null\n114\t      },\n115\t      {\n116\t        \"id\": \"AC13\",\n117\t        \"covered\": true,\n118\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_does_not_reset_usage_and_events_uncapped\",\n119\t        \"reason\": \"Directly reads the raw usage_rollup row before and after the DELETE and asserts total_quantity is byte-identical (5 both times), then proves the cap is genuinely gone by POSTing a 9999-quantity event that would have 429'd under the old cap=10 and asserting 201.\",\n120\t        \"delegated\": null\n121\t      },\n122\t      {\n123\t        \"id\": \"AC14\",\n124\t        \"covered\": true,\n125\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_no_new_alembic_migration_added\",\n126\t        \"reason\": \"Negative assertion: lists alembic/versions/*.py and asserts exactly 3 files exist (0001-0003), so a stray new migration would fail this test. Existing PUT/events/usage suites all still pass unchanged in this same full run.\",\n127\t        \"delegated\": null\n128\t      },\n129\t      {\n130\t        \"id\": \"AC15\",\n131\t        \"covered\": true,\n132\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py::test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent (+ security stage's Semgrep parameterized-SQL check)\",\n133\t        \"reason\": \"Same backstop-disabling test as AC8 -- issues the DELETE via a NOBYPASSRLS role with the api_key_id predicate stripped entirely and shows RLS alone still confines it. The parameterized-text()-bind-params claim (no string-built SQL) is a static/Semgrep concern, appropriately left to the security stage's 6c check rather than duplicated here as a test assertion.\",\n134\t        \"delegated\": null\n135\t      },\n136\t      {\n137\t        \"id\": \"AC16\",\n138\t        \"covered\": true,\n139\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_and_forbidden_are_logged\",\n140\t        \"reason\": \"capsys-captured stdout asserts BOTH `quota.delete` is present with `***redacted***` in place of the raw customer_id (proving the structlog facade's centralized redaction fired, per src/logging/__init__.py's _REDACT list which includes customer_id) AND `quota.forbidden` fires on the ingest-key GET.\",\n141\t        \"delegated\": null\n142\t      },\n143\t      {\n144\t        \"id\": \"AC17\",\n145\t        \"covered\": true,\n146\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_openapi_exposes_get_and_delete_quotas + tests/test_dast_context_documented.py::test_bearer_split_token_auth_context_is_documented\",\n147\t        \"reason\": \"First test asserts /openapi.json actually contains both new operations (served schema, not a hand claim); second (pre-existing, still passing) asserts the documented Bearer split-token auth context.\",\n148\t        \"delegated\": null\n149\t      },\n150\t      {\n151\t        \"id\": \"AC18\",\n152\t        \"covered\": false,\n153\t        \"test\": \"\",\n154\t        \"reason\": \"ASVS 5.0.0 reconciliation across the change set is the security stage's deliverable, not a test-suite assertion (per acceptance.md frontmatter delegated_criteria). Copied verbatim from acceptance.md, not invented here.\",\n155\t        \"delegated\": \"security\"\n156\t      },\n157\t      {\n158\t        \"id\": \"AC19\",\n159\t        \"covered\": true,\n160\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope + ::test_delete_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed\",\n161\t        \"reason\": \"Both monkeypatch the service-layer function to raise RuntimeError and use ASGITransport(raise_app_exceptions=False) to force the real error-handler path; both assert 500/code:internal/requestId present and that the exception class name and message text never leak into the response. The DELETE variant additionally re-reads the raw quotas row afterward and asserts limit_per_window is untouched (42), proving the transaction actually rolled back (fail-closed), not merely that the HTTP response looked generic.\",\n162\t        \"delegated\": null\n163\t      }\n164\t    ]\n165\t  },\n166\t  \"resilience\": {\n167\t    \"migration_roundtrip\": \"n/a\",\n168\t    \"property_tests\": 2,\n169\t    \"concurrency\": \"pass\"\n170\t  },\n171\t  \"resilience_note\": \"migration_roundtrip: n/a -- no migration files in this change set (AC14 asserts this negatively, verified above). property_tests: 2 Hypothesis tests total in tests/test_schemas_quotas.py (1 pre-existing for QuotaPutRequest, unchanged; 1 NEW for QuotaDeleteParams -- test_property_delete_customer_id_only_ever_accepts_the_allowlist -- added by this diff), each generating up to 300-char arbitrary text and asserting acceptance implies the anchored regex. concurrency: tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_concurrent_delete_of_the_same_quota_yields_exactly_one_winner fires 10 concurrent DELETEs at the identical (customer_id, metric) via asyncio.gather and asserts the LOSER's outcome explicitly (exactly one 204, the rest 404, never a 500/race artifact, and the row count is exactly 0 afterward) -- the strong form, not merely 'exactly one row exists'. Not an acceptance criterion on its own (AC6/AC7 already cover the single-caller 204/404 contract), so it does not ride criteria_covered, but is reported per the adversarial-shape convention for a DB-mutating decision point.\",\n172\t  \"perf\": {\n173\t    \"budget\": {\n174\t      \"p95_ms\": null,\n175\t      \"throughput_rps\": null\n176\t    },\n177\t    \"measured\": {\n178\t      \"p95_ms\": null,\n179\t      \"throughput_rps\": null\n180\t    },\n181\t    \"scenario\": null,\n182\t    \"status\": \"n/a\"\n183\t  },\n184\t  \"coverage\": {\n185\t    \"combined\": {\n186\t      \"lines\": 88.15,\n187\t      \"branches\": 66.67,\n188\t      \"functions\": null\n189\t    },\n190\t    \"unit\": {\n191\t      \"lines\": null,\n192\t      \"branches\": null\n193\t    },\n194\t    \"integration\": {\n195\t      \"lines\": null,\n196\t      \"branches\": null\n197\t    }\n198\t  },\n199\t  \"coverage_note\": \"Single combined pytest+coverage run (unit and integration tests share one process/coverage context; no out-of-process/testcontainers-separate-process merge needed here since testcontainers Postgres/Redis are accessed from the same in-process pytest run via httpx ASGITransport, not a separate service under test). Per-suite unit/integration split not separately instrumented this run (would require --cov-context=test and per-context extraction not currently configured) -- omitted per 'best-effort'. New/changed feature modules (src/api/routes/quotas.py, src/api/schemas/quotas.py, src/services/quota_service.py) are 100% line-covered; src/repositories/quotas_repo.py shows 71% branch coverage but the 5 flagged lines are either (a) pre-existing lines 84-85 untouched by this diff, or (b) this feature's own return statements (180, 215) that ARE exercised by every call-path test (empty list, multi-row list, delete-found=True, delete-not-found=False) -- a coverage.py partial-branch artifact on multi-line comprehension/return statements, matching the identical pre-existing pattern already present on the sibling read_tenant_quota_state_locked function (verified by reading the source this session). Functions percentage not reported: coverage.py's default line/branch report does not emit a distinct function-coverage metric in this project's configuration.\",\n200\t  \"docker_dependency_note\": \"Integration suite requires Docker (testcontainers Postgres/Redis). Verified this session: Docker Desktop was not running at task start (`docker ps` failed with a named-pipe connection error); started it and polled `docker ps` until ready (~1 min) before running the suite.\"\n201\t}\n202\t"}]},"uuid":"50c9042f-ddca-4ce8-a3bf-970646f823aa","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:26:14.866Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/test-results.json","content":"{\n  \"status\": \"pass\",\n  \"ran_at\": \"2026-07-10T03:49:38Z\",\n  \"scope\": \"diff\",\n  \"since_commit\": \"ef3fb3f686649d0ee0d37707dd61013b5e1d28f4\",\n  \"tested_change_hash\": \"a5ab12805cc7429fcb55d5b55da7b8663f4bf011c45f3635394f099f989dd308\",\n  \"test_strategy\": \"pyramid\",\n  \"total\": 217,\n  \"passed\": 216,\n  \"failed\": 1,\n  \"skipped\": {\n    \"count\": 0,\n    \"tests\": []\n  },\n  \"failures\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py::test_export_p95_timing_meets_the_confirmed_3000ms_budget_at_the_row_cap\",\n      \"reason\": \"Pre-existing test from the already-merged usage-export feature (git log shows its last touch at commit bcf16bb, before this branch's diff); it is NOT part of the quota-admin change set (verified this session via `git diff HEAD --name-only` / `git log -- <file>` — the file is untouched by this branch). It is a hard-coded wall-clock p95<=3000ms assert with NO @pytest.mark.perf marker (verified: no perf marker registered anywhere in pyproject.toml or tests/, confirmed via grep this session), so it is not excluded by `-m \\\"not perf\\\"` and also runs unfiltered in pipeline-ci.yml's `poetry run pytest --cov=src --cov-branch --cov-fail-under=85` (no -m flag there either). Re-ran it in isolation twice this session: p95 measured 3763.02ms and similarly over-budget both times, on a dev machine that had four unrelated Docker containers already running concurrently (compounds-openfga, postgres-dev, openemr, phpmyadmin — confirmed via `docker ps` this session) competing for CPU alongside the freshly-started testcontainers Postgres/Redis. This matches the exact machine-load-flake pattern implementation's own progress notes recorded for the sibling test_perf_k6_load.py during this same feature's development. This is a pre-existing, out-of-scope regression risk (its budget was set from a different, less-loaded measurement session) and a real M4P-10 gap (unmarked hard timing assert riding the CI merge gate) — flagged for the human/deployment owner as a follow-up, not fixed here (fixing it would mean editing an unrelated file's test infra / CI config outside this feature's diff, and this session's evidence does not distinguish 'the perf regressed' from 'this dev box was busy' cleanly enough to safely retune the budget).\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"tests_by_type\": {\n    \"unit\": 6,\n    \"integration\": 20,\n    \"e2e\": 0\n  },\n  \"tests_by_type_note\": \"Counts are the NEW tests added for this feature (6 in tests/test_schemas_quotas.py::QuotaDeleteParams cases; 19 in tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py + 1 new backstop test appended to tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py). Full-suite composition (pre-existing + new) totals 217 tests. The plan declares `pyramid` with an explicit integration-heavy bias for this feature's own tier split (plan.md 'Test strategy' section) because the guarantees under test — ordering, tenant isolation, RLS backstop, fail-closed rollback, per-principal throttling — are only real against actual Postgres/Redis; the schema/validation-only logic (QuotaDeleteParams) stayed unit. This matches the plan's stated rationale, not a silent drift from pyramid.\",\n  \"criteria_covered\": {\n    \"total\": 19,\n    \"covered\": 18,\n    \"by_id\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC1\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_lists_tenant_quotas_ordered_minimal_fields\",\n        \"reason\": \"Seeds 3 rows out of insertion order across two customers; asserts exact response body (order + minimal 3-key field set), not just status code.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC2\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_is_tenant_isolated\",\n        \"reason\": \"Two real tenants (distinct api_key_id), tenant A's GET list asserted to contain only its own row.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC3\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_empty_returns_200_empty_list\",\n        \"reason\": \"Fresh tenant, no quotas seeded, asserts 200 + [] (not 404).\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC4\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_ingest_key_forbidden\",\n        \"reason\": \"Ingest-scoped key against GET asserts 403 forbidden envelope.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC5\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_requires_auth\",\n        \"reason\": \"Both no-Authorization-header and an invalid bearer token asserted 401 on GET.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC6\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_existing_returns_204_and_removes_row\",\n        \"reason\": \"204 + empty body asserted, then verified via a subsequent GET and a direct raw-table COUNT(*) that the row is actually gone (not merely a status-code check).\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC7\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_absent_returns_404_envelope\",\n        \"reason\": \"DELETE of a never-seeded (customer_id, metric) asserts 404 not_found, proving the explicit-404 (non-idempotent) decision.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC8\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_cannot_touch_other_tenant + tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py::test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent\",\n        \"reason\": \"The app-level test proves the IDOR/BOLA outcome (A deleting B's row -> 404, B's row survives) through the real route. The backstop test independently proves WHY: it drops the api_key_id filter entirely and connects as a NOBYPASSRLS role mirroring prod's meterly_app role, and shows the FORCE RLS policy alone still confines the unfiltered DELETE to the caller's tenant -- the adversarial 'disable the primary control, prove the backstop fires' shape, not merely a pass with both controls intact.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC9\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_schemas_quotas.py (QuotaDeleteParams: accepts/missing/mass-assignment/injection-oversized/invalid-metric/hypothesis-property cases) + tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_validation_rejections\",\n        \"reason\": \"Unit tier proves the schema boundary in isolation (allowlist regex, extra='forbid', SQLi/traversal/CRLF/oversized payloads all rejected pre-DB); the integration test proves the same rejections surface as 422 validation_failed end-to-end including the unknown-extra-query-param case (api_key_id=999).\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC10\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_ingest_key_forbidden\",\n        \"reason\": \"Ingest-scoped key against DELETE asserts 403 forbidden.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC11\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_requires_auth\",\n        \"reason\": \"Both missing and malformed bearer token asserted 401 on DELETE.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC12\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_quota_admin_routes_rate_limited_per_principal\",\n        \"reason\": \"The discriminating adversarial shape: two admin principals share ONE client IP (ASGITransport pinned to 10.0.0.9). Principal A (1 req/s) gets 429 on its second GET; principal B (100 req/s), same IP, still succeeds on both GET and DELETE -- proving the bucket is keyed on api_key_id, not IP. A same-IP-different-owner assertion, not merely 'a different owner on a different IP is unaffected'.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC13\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_does_not_reset_usage_and_events_uncapped\",\n        \"reason\": \"Directly reads the raw usage_rollup row before and after the DELETE and asserts total_quantity is byte-identical (5 both times), then proves the cap is genuinely gone by POSTing a 9999-quantity event that would have 429'd under the old cap=10 and asserting 201.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC14\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_no_new_alembic_migration_added\",\n        \"reason\": \"Negative assertion: lists alembic/versions/*.py and asserts exactly 3 files exist (0001-0003), so a stray new migration would fail this test. Existing PUT/events/usage suites all still pass unchanged in this same full run.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC15\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py::test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent (+ security stage's Semgrep parameterized-SQL check)\",\n        \"reason\": \"Same backstop-disabling test as AC8 -- issues the DELETE via a NOBYPASSRLS role with the api_key_id predicate stripped entirely and shows RLS alone still confines it. The parameterized-text()-bind-params claim (no string-built SQL) is a static/Semgrep concern, appropriately left to the security stage's 6c check rather than duplicated here as a test assertion.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC16\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_and_forbidden_are_logged\",\n        \"reason\": \"capsys-captured stdout asserts BOTH `quota.delete` is present with `***redacted***` in place of the raw customer_id (proving the structlog facade's centralized redaction fired, per src/logging/__init__.py's _REDACT list which includes customer_id) AND `quota.forbidden` fires on the ingest-key GET.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC17\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_openapi_exposes_get_and_delete_quotas + tests/test_dast_context_documented.py::test_bearer_split_token_auth_context_is_documented\",\n        \"reason\": \"First test asserts /openapi.json actually contains both new operations (served schema, not a hand claim); second (pre-existing, still passing) asserts the documented Bearer split-token auth context.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC18\",\n        \"covered\": false,\n        \"test\": \"\",\n        \"reason\": \"ASVS 5.0.0 reconciliation across the change set is the security stage's deliverable, not a test-suite assertion (per acceptance.md frontmatter delegated_criteria). Copied verbatim from acceptance.md, not invented here.\",\n        \"delegated\": \"security\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"AC19\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope + ::test_delete_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed\",\n        \"reason\": \"Both monkeypatch the service-layer function to raise RuntimeError and use ASGITransport(raise_app_exceptions=False) to force the real error-handler path; both assert 500/code:internal/requestId present and that the exception class name and message text never leak into the response. The DELETE variant additionally re-reads the raw quotas row afterward and asserts limit_per_window is untouched (42), proving the transaction actually rolled back (fail-closed), not merely that the HTTP response looked generic.\",\n        \"delegated\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"resilience\": {\n    \"migration_roundtrip\": \"n/a\",\n    \"property_tests\": 2,\n    \"concurrency\": \"pass\"\n  },\n  \"resilience_note\": \"migration_roundtrip: n/a -- no migration files in this change set (AC14 asserts this negatively, verified above). property_tests: 2 Hypothesis tests total in tests/test_schemas_quotas.py (1 pre-existing for QuotaPutRequest, unchanged; 1 NEW for QuotaDeleteParams -- test_property_delete_customer_id_only_ever_accepts_the_allowlist -- added by this diff), each generating up to 300-char arbitrary text and asserting acceptance implies the anchored regex. concurrency: tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_concurrent_delete_of_the_same_quota_yields_exactly_one_winner fires 10 concurrent DELETEs at the identical (customer_id, metric) via asyncio.gather and asserts the LOSER's outcome explicitly (exactly one 204, the rest 404, never a 500/race artifact, and the row count is exactly 0 afterward) -- the strong form, not merely 'exactly one row exists'. Not an acceptance criterion on its own (AC6/AC7 already cover the single-caller 204/404 contract), so it does not ride criteria_covered, but is reported per the adversarial-shape convention for a DB-mutating decision point.\",\n  \"perf\": {\n    \"budget\": {\n      \"p95_ms\": null,\n      \"throughput_rps\": null\n    },\n    \"measured\": {\n      \"p95_ms\": null,\n      \"throughput_rps\": null\n    },\n    \"scenario\": null,\n    \"status\": \"n/a\"\n  },\n  \"coverage\": {\n    \"combined\": {\n      \"lines\": 88.15,\n      \"branches\": 66.67,\n      \"functions\": null\n    },\n    \"unit\": {\n      \"lines\": null,\n      \"branches\": null\n    },\n    \"integration\": {\n      \"lines\": null,\n      \"branches\": null\n    }\n  },\n  \"coverage_note\": \"Single combined pytest+coverage run (unit and integration tests share one process/coverage context; no out-of-process/testcontainers-separate-process merge needed here since testcontainers Postgres/Redis are accessed from the same in-process pytest run via httpx ASGITransport, not a separate service under test). Per-suite unit/integration split not separately instrumented this run (would require --cov-context=test and per-context extraction not currently configured) -- omitted per 'best-effort'. New/changed feature modules (src/api/routes/quotas.py, src/api/schemas/quotas.py, src/services/quota_service.py) are 100% line-covered; src/repositories/quotas_repo.py shows 71% branch coverage but the 5 flagged lines are either (a) pre-existing lines 84-85 untouched by this diff, or (b) this feature's own return statements (180, 215) that ARE exercised by every call-path test (empty list, multi-row list, delete-found=True, delete-not-found=False) -- a coverage.py partial-branch artifact on multi-line comprehension/return statements, matching the identical pre-existing pattern already present on the sibling read_tenant_quota_state_locked function (verified by reading the source this session). Functions percentage not reported: coverage.py's default line/branch report does not emit a distinct function-coverage metric in this project's configuration.\",\n  \"docker_dependency_note\": \"Integration suite requires Docker (testcontainers Postgres/Redis). Verified this session: Docker Desktop was not running at task start (`docker ps` failed with a named-pipe connection error); started it and polled `docker ps` until ready (~1 min) before running the suite.\"\n}\n","numLines":202,"startLine":1,"totalLines":202}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"82ac8b80-85c7-4136-9b0a-31746d986d07","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
