r a customer_id supplied as an array-like bracket syntax). FastAPI's Query() binding for a str field on repeated params is worth a boundary test given DELETE takes only query params (no body) and typed coercion mistakes are exactly the class of bug allowlist-based schemas are meant to catch.\",\n        \"severity\": \"low\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"area\": \"quotas_repo.list_quotas / delete_quota - ordering under NULL or duplicate collisions\",\n        \"gap\": \"AC1's ordering test seeds three distinct (customer_id, metric) pairs; it never seeds two rows differing only by metric under case-insensitive-adjacent values (e.g. 'API' vs 'api') to prove the RDS default collation genuinely produces a stable order across runs (plan's own open question 2 flags this as an accepted risk, not resolved) -- current tests can't distinguish 'stable because ORDER BY is present' from 'stable because the specific seeded values happen to sort unambiguously under any collation'.\",\n        \"severity\": \"low\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"area\": \"AC19 / GET safe-error path\",\n        \"gap\": \"The GET forced-error test monkeypatches quota_service.list_quotas at the service layer, which is one level above the actual DB I/O (quotas_repo.list_quotas). It proves the route -> error-handler wiring, but doesn't force a failure inside the repository's own text()-execute call (e.g. a real asyncpg DBAPIError) to prove the repository layer itself doesn't leak a raw SQLSTATE/DSN fragment before the service-level catch. The DELETE variant has the same shape but is partially compensated by its own fail-closed row-survival assertion, which does exercise real DB state.\",\n        \"severity\": \"low\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"area\": \"Mutation coverage\",\n        \"gap\": \"No mutation run has ever executed against quotas_repo.py/quota_service.py/routes/quotas.py/schemas/quotas.py (see mutation.note) -- so 100%-branch-covered lines in these modules are unverified against e.g. an off-by-one in the ORDER BY clause, a flipped 404-vs-204 boundary condition, or a swapped AND/OR in delete_quota's WHERE clause. Line/branch coverage alone cannot catch a mutant that changes behavior without changing which lines execute (e.g. AND -> OR in the WHERE clause would still hit the same lines).\",\n        \"severity\": \"medium\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n","numLines":45,"startLine":1,"totalLines":45}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a14ef82e-70af-40ad-8858-41d896b6738a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
